<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:02AM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Bourbon
and northwestern Crawford Counties through 345 AM CDT...
At 302 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Moran, or 10 miles south of La Harpe, moving southeast
at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Walnut...                         Hepler...
Hiattville...                     Porterville...
Petersburg...                     Brazilton...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
